[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ByteDance has officially released a brand new version of their AI video tool Seedance. There\'s a brand new Omni tool on the market that allows you to make changes to your footage in real time. Runway and Magnific are now integrated'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'into Chat GPT and there\'s a brand new image generator that is actually kind of better than other image generators on the market and the best part is it gives you editing control just like Photoshop.'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Welcome to AI film news. My name is Caleb. Thank you so much for joining us. Be sure to like and subscribe if you want more AI videos like this directly here on the platform. So, before we get'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going, I want to give a hat tip to the Curious Refuge community in London who hosted a meet up this last week and Runway for hosting Dave Clark, who\'s the chief creative officer here at Promise'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Studios. So, without further ado, let\'s get to the news. The first big bit of news that I want to talk about this week comes from the people at ByteDance. So, the team has released Seedance Mini and'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it is officially live on Drimena and CapCut. The value proposition really is that this brand new model should be about 75% faster than the existing version of Seedance 2.0 and 55%'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cheaper. But, don\'t take my word for it. Let\'s hop into the tool and see it in action. So, I\'m here on the Drimena website and at the bottom, you can see we have AI video selected. Now, I'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'brought in a first frame here and this is actually an example that I talked about a couple weeks ago. We have this Revolutionary War scene and essentially, I\'ve prompted for multiple shots'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'back-to-back where I went into more detail about what I want to see from the changes in the camera angle. Now, at the very bottom, you\'ll see we have this menu and we have Seedance 2.0 Mini. So, we\'ll go ahead and select it. And from'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here, if you go all the way to the side, you can also change the duration. You can generate the video clips up to 15 seconds long, and you can see that it will cost 40 credits to generate this video clip, and go ahead and click'

[02:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'render. So, again, this was our starting image, and this is the video that we got from C Dance mini. Okay, so there\'s some things to like in'

[02:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'typical C Dance form, the physics look really nice, but I will say there is quite a lot of artifacting that\'s happening over the video footage, and the skin texturing in the face is really'

[02:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'coming across as very plasticky and synthetic, which really makes it very similar to Google VEO, which can struggle very much [music] with the exact same thing. Now, let\'s go ahead and compare this mini model to the'

[02:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'traditional C Dance 2.0 model to see how they stack up. So, this is from C Dance 2.0, the regular [music] version. And I got to say C Dance 2.0 is much much better, and I think in a professional'

[03:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'capacity, I don\'t really see why you would want to use mini versus the existing and already established and really awesome version of C Dance 2.0, especially because C Dance 2.0 &gt;&gt; [music]'

[03:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; regular gives you the ability to generate the video clip in up to 1080p, which is just really helpful if you are working on a professional project. It also has better physics and less banding in my opinion, but let\'s take a look at'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a couple more examples here. So, I have this storyboard here, and I prompted for an entire scene from a single C Dance clip. Again, this is not multiple shots, this is a single source asset and a'

[03:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video that was automatically generated. So, we got this from C Dance mini. Okay, uh not really adhering to the 180°'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'rule and there\'s uh just some funny physics happening, but the fact that we typed in a prompt and got that just from a single storyboard image is kind of impressive, I suppose. But, let\'s take a'

[04:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'look at the version we got from SeaDance. That\'s what I\'m talking about. That'

[04:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'looks uh really, really good. I think with two or three different generations in that style, if you brought it into an editing system and cut it together, it would look like an incredibly professional fight scene. It did a'

[04:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really, really nice job. Now, let\'s take a look at our final example here. So, I\'m going to do this wide shot because, you know, AI just really struggles at small details, crowd shots. It can be really, really tricky. So, here is an'

[04:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image of a Viking on a battlefield here. I don\'t know how accurate this is to history, but you know what, we\'re just going to go with it. Okay. So, I prompted for a scene where that main Viking goes running with his axe'

[05:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'throughout the scene. This is what we got from SeaDance Mini. &gt;&gt; [screaming]'

[05:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[groaning] &gt;&gt; Okay, I\'m glad that axe blow was uh off screen there. I think that preserved our rating here. Now, let\'s take a look at'

[05:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the same version inside SeaDance 2.0. &gt;&gt; [screaming] &gt;&gt; The physics are unbelievable. I do think'

[05:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the characters in the background have some problems with continuity here, but the fact that you can get that entire shot from a single image and prompt inside a video model in the very first generation, it\'s amazing how far we\'ve'

[06:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'come in just 3 years. 3 years ago, you were having to basically do 2D puppet tool animation inside of combinations between like After Effects and other visual effects software, and now you can'

[06:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use photorealistic imagery to create scenes using multi-shot prompts in advanced video models that are actually somehow better at dynamic fight scenes and physics than just regular'

[06:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'conversation scenes. It\'s absolutely a wild time to be alive. Now, from our initial test of SeaDance Mini, we saw that it took about 3 minutes to generate the video clip, and the cost can get'

[06:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'much cheaper, but if you just take a normal credit pack from Dreemina and break it down based on the credits and the dollar and cents, it cost us about $1.60 to create a 15-second clip. So,'

[06:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'roughly about 50 cents to create a 5-second clip, which is cheap, but again, if you\'re now picking between a really, really good video and one that\'s pretty impressive, it\'s going to be hard'

[07:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to justify utilizing the mini version versus just the regular version. But, of course, it all just depends on the budget of the project that you are working on. And speaking of Dreemina, they also released their agentic'

[07:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'workflow platform called Octo. Octo is essentially a tool that allows you to type in a prompt, and it\'s a creative agent that works with you inside a canvas experience. Now, very similar to'

[07:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'all of these agentic canvas approaches that we\'ve tested here at Curious Refuge, from our test, I don\'t see why you would want to use this AI agentic experience because it is very slow and'

[07:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it misses a lot of the nuance. So, in my opinion, it\'s still better just to use the aggregators in the traditional application view, but it is worth checking out and they did include a breakdown from PJA Ace where he used the'

[07:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tool on an upcoming film that he\'s working on called Nexus. I highly recommend checking it out. Curious Refuge is teaming up with CapCut to host an AI workshop on the latest AI workflows directly inside [music]'

[08:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the CapCut ecosystem. If you want to see how AI is integrated, especially in a then mark your calendars for Thursday, June 25th at 11:00 a.m. Pacific time. You can RSVP'

[08:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'completely for free by clicking the link below this video. Now, speaking of tool news, we also saw this last week that Chat GPT and Claude now include Runway and Magnific inside their MCP'

[08:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'integrations. What does this mean? Well, long story short, when you\'re inside of either one of those LLMs, it could be Chat GPT or Claude, you can integrate the application so that it uses your'

[08:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'credits and you don\'t actually have to leave the language model in order to create your videos or the images using the aggregators. It\'s pretty cool. Let me show you how to get it set up and'

[09:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we\'ll use it for a couple examples here. So, for this example, I\'m going to use Chat GPT, but you can totally use Claude if you want to. So, first let\'s go to apps on the left side here and all you have to do is search for the application'

[09:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'re looking for, whether it\'s Runway or Magnific. They also have a ton of apps on their website that you can connect inside of the apps window here. So, I\'m going to search for Runway.'

[09:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We\'ll go ahead and select the Runway app and you can see we can go ahead and click this start chat button. And now you can see we have the Runway icon in the bottom left. If you\'re starting a'

[09:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'completely new chat, you can just hit the plus button and go over here to more and then select Runway, and it will do the exact same thing. So, I\'m going to do a very quick example here. We\'re going to say create a 16 by 9 video of a'

[09:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'woman who has brave trepidation saying, "I know who you are. This ends tonight." Let\'s also bring in an image here. So, I have this image that was generated'

[10:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'inside of Midjourney, and we want to animate it inside of Runway. And when you\'re ready, go ahead and click send prompt. And after a couple minutes, that gives us this video clip here.'

[10:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; I know who you are. This ends tonight. &gt;&gt; Okay, it\'s fine. The physics and the acting are okay, but there\'s a lot to be desired, and there\'s just a lot of'

[10:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'texturing, again, a lot of plastic qualities coming through on the face here. Now, let\'s compare that same generation to SeaDance just to create some perspective here. Again, this is'

[10:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the regular 2.0 version. That gave us this. &gt;&gt; I know who you are. This ends tonight. &gt;&gt; Okay, not too sure why it got cut off there, but the the physics, and'

[10:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'especially the hyper-sharpening around the edges of the character, are just a little bit better inside of SeaDance here. Now, the same is also true with Magnific here. So, we\'re inside of ChatGPT. I\'ve already added the application, so we\'ll go to more and'

[11:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then select Magnific here, and we can have a back-and-forth conversational experience. So, earlier I said create a multi-panel shot of a man on a white background wearing a red resort wear shirt. Create various angles of the man,'

[11:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'because whenever you are working on a film project, you almost always need to define what your character looks like by creating a character sheet. And that gave us this image here. And so we were able to have a back and forth'

[11:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'conversational experience, and because it\'s Magnific, it\'s integrated with all sorts of other image generation and video generation tools directly inside of the platform. Now, with all of that being said, it does seem like most of'

[11:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these language models are creating application integrations &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; directly inside of their tool. But in my opinion, from playing around with these tools, whether it\'s an MCP inside an AI language model or an agentic workflow'

[12:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'inside a canvas experience, really none of them have the speed that I would really want inside a creative workflow. It does seem like there\'s something'

[12:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there, and I do think there are some creative one-shot examples of integrating an application directly inside the language model to help save you some time. But if you\'re working on a film project and you really need to organize a bunch of different shots, and'

[12:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it\'s going to take a lot of iteration, I do think just the classic aggregation workflow is still probably your best bet. The team at Eleven Labs now has an AI avatar tool built directly inside of'

[12:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'their platform. Long story short, you now have the ability to clone a character and a voice using Eleven Labs or other tools on the market and [music] do automatic lip-sync to create a video,'

[12:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'whether it\'s an influencer video, talking head, or anything [music] in between. Let\'s take a look at how to use the tool and see how it stacks up. To use the new avatar tool, all you have to do is go to elevenlabs.io,'

[13:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and then on the left side we\'ll go to image and [music] video. Now, from here, we\'re going to create a brand new avatar. And you can see you can either type in a prompt to create an avatar, or'

[13:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can upload images to create your own clone. So I have a few different images here of this nerd that I want to clone, and we\'ll go ahead and drag and drop the images into 11 Labs. And from here, we'

[13:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can give him a name, and then select the voice. So, I actually had 11 Labs a couple years ago do some voice cloning. The quality is much better now, but we\'ll go ahead and use my cloned voice'

[13:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'directly here in 11 Labs, and go ahead and select create avatar. And from here, it will create a very basic version of your avatar, and then you can create a new style to put them in a new'

[13:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'background or in a completely new scene with different composition. It really just depends on you. So, we can go in here to prompt it, and we can describe where we want our character to be. So, I can say a man standing in front of a'

[14:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'modern YouTube studio background, and you can select selfie or third-person. We\'ll do third-person, of course, and 16 by 9, and go ahead and select create style. And then after a few seconds, we have this image of this guy that like is'

[14:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'maybe like 95% me. It\'s not quite right. Like there\'s something just a little off about this guy, but it\'s pretty close. So, I think it did a pretty good job here. Now, I created a couple backgrounds earlier.'

[14:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'m going to select this more modern kind of office style background here, and we brought it inside of our avatar section here. Now, for speech, you do have the ability to use 11 Labs to'

[14:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generate the audio that would be get connected to the lip sync tool here, or you can also bring in your own audio. So, it could be audio of your subject like me talking to the camera here or talking into a microphone because I'

